<paragraph blockId="10.[178,1085,256,336]" pageId="10" pageNumber="939">
R e m a r k s: this species does not seem to occur in eastern 
<collectingCountry box="[817,893,256,278]" name="Turkey" pageId="10" pageNumber="939">Turkey</collectingCountry>
. The larvae live in the roots of 
<taxonomicName box="[306,464,285,307]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Ononis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="10" pageNumber="939" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="spinosa">
<emphasis box="[306,464,285,307]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="939">Ononis spinosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or an 
<taxonomicName box="[533,685,285,307]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Ononis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="10" pageNumber="939" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[533,606,285,307]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="939">Ononis</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
that resembles this plant strongly, and in the roots of 
<emphasis box="[325,535,314,336]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="939">Psoralea bituminosa</emphasis>
(KALLIES in litt.).
</paragraph>
